<h3 id=3D"MonitoringinwestpacMesh-HowareweusingSplunkinWestpacMesh?"><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);">How are we using Splunk in Westpac Mesh?</s=
pan></h3>
<p class=3D"p1">Splunk is a primary tool for monitoring API traffic and rel=
ated metrics in Mesh, and it can be highly effective in this context for se=
veral reasons:</p>
<p class=3D"p2"><br></p>
<p><strong>Comprehensive Data Collection:</strong> Splunk can collect and i=
ndex a wide range of data sources, including API logs, gateway logs, and ot=
her relevant metrics. This allows for a centralised view of all API-related=
 activities, making it easier to track and analyze traffic patterns.</p>
<p class=3D"p1"><strong>Powerful Search and Query Capabilities:</strong> Sp=
lunk's search language (SPL) is highly versatile and allows you to query yo=
ur data in a variety of ways. This is particularly useful for API monitorin=
g, as you can create complex queries to filter and analyze traffic, respons=
e times, and error rates. For instance, you can search for specific API end=
points, track usage over time, or identify performance bottlenecks.</p>
<p class=3D"p1"><strong>Customisable Dashboards and Alerts:</strong> With S=
plunk, you can create custom dashboards to visualize API traffic and perfor=
mance metrics in a way that is most relevant to your needs. You can set up =
alerts to notify you of specific conditions, such as high response times, e=
rror rates, or unusual traffic spikes, ensuring you can respond quickly to =
potential issues.</p>
<p class=3D"p1"><strong>&nbsp;Historical Data Analysis: </strong>Splunk all=
ows you to store and analyse historical data, which is crucial for identify=
ing trends and patterns over time. For APIs, this means you can analyse his=
torical traffic patterns, assess long-term performance trends, and make dat=
a-driven decisions to optimize your APIs.</p>
<p class=3D"p1"><strong>Correlation of Data:</strong> Splunk can correlate =
data from multiple sources, such as API logs, gateway logs, and application=
 performance metrics. This correlation capability helps in understanding th=
e full context of issues, such as how changes in API traffic might be impac=
ting response times or how gateway performance might be influencing overall=
 API performance.</p>
<p class=3D"p1"><strong>Scalability: </strong>As your API traffic grows, Sp=
lunk can scale to handle larger volumes of data. This scalability ensures t=
hat you can continue to monitor and analyse API performance effectively, ev=
en as your environment becomes more complex.</p>
<p class=3D"p1">In summary, Splunk provides a robust and flexible platform =
for monitoring API traffic by offering real-time visibility, powerful searc=
h and query capabilities, customisable dashboards, and the ability to handl=
e large volumes of data. These features make it an excellent choice for gai=
ning comprehensive insights into API performance and ensuring optimal opera=
tion.</p>
<h3 id=3D"MonitoringinwestpacMesh-WhyareweusingSplunk?"><span style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(34,34,34);">Why are we using Splunk ?</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>We are running very large platform serving 100Million+ transactions per=
 day.&nbsp; Thousands of API are talking to each other and generating large=
 amount of log files with critical information, error etc.&nbsp;</li>
<li>We are also hosting thousands of servers serving as containers and gate=
ways. Which needs high computation with large number of CPUs and Memory to =
serve these transactions. There will be huge business impact if the servers=
 goes down due to lack of capacity. we must be able to monitor health of ou=
r servers and get alerted when there is a red flag.</li>
<li>Our data volume is close to 1 TB/Day.</li>
<li>We need visibility into these machine generated unstructured data and&n=
bsp;perform stats, aggregations or find a meaningful insights at one single=
 place with ease of access.</li>
</ul>
