<h5 style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"MonitoringinwestpacMesh-GeneralSea=
rchPractices-Wildcards:"><strong>General Search Practices - Wildcards:</str=
ong></h5>
<ul>
<li>Splunk only searches for whole words, but wildcards allowed.</li>
<li>Only Trailing wildcards make efficient use of index.=20
<ul>
<li>Wildcards at beginning of string scan all events within time frame</li>
<li>Wildcards in middle of string may return inconsistent results</li>
<li>so use<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,255);"> fail*</span><span style=3D"=
color: rgb(255,0,0);"> ( not *fail or&nbsp;<strong>fail</strong>&nbsp; or f=
*il)</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li>Inclusion is generally better than exclusion=20
<ul>
<li>Searching for <span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,255);">"failed transaction"=
</span> is faster than <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">NOT "success tr=
ansaction"</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li>Filter as early in your search as possible=20
<ul>
<li>Remove duplicates then sorting is faster than sorting then removing dup=
licates</li>
</ul></li>
<li>use appropriate search mode - Fast / Smart / Verbose</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
