<ul>
<li>When a search returns statistical values, results can be viewed with a =
wide variety of visualization types.=20
<ul>
<li>Statistics table</li>
<li>Charts: line, column, pie, etc</li>
<li>Single value, gauges</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>timechart Command - Overview :</p>
<ul>
<li>timechart command performs statistical aggregations against time</li>
<li>Plots and trends data over time</li>
<li>_time is always the x-axis</li>
<li>you can optionally split data using the by clause for one other field=
=20
<ul>
<li>Each distinct value of the split by field is a separate series in the c=
hart</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Timecharts are best represented as line or area charts</li>
</ul>
<p>Examples :</p>
<p>Scenario : which day is a peak day in terms of daily API hits? How many =
days are performing above or below moving Average?</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);">index=3Dprd_summary source=3DMes=
h_platform_daily_hits_summary&nbsp;</span><br><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,=
102,255);">| table platform_hits &nbsp;_time&nbsp;</span><br><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(51,102,255);">| timechart span=3D1d sum(platform_hits) as total=
_hits&nbsp;</span><br><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);">| eval date_w=
day=3Dlower(strftime(_time,"%A"))&nbsp;</span><br><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(51,102,255);">| &nbsp;eval trend=3Dtotal_hits</span><br><span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(51,102,255);">| fields _time &nbsp;total_hits trend</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
